stars\nhaving orbital periods shorter than 1000 days is at least 10 %, and possibly as\nhigh as 20 %, if the majority of CEMP stars are formed in such short-period\nbinaries. This result suggests that the period distribution of EMP binary\nsystems is biased toward short periods, unless the binary fraction of low-mass\nEMP stars is significantly higher than that of other nearby stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Oct 2014 05:17:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
